abstract = {Early studies of the impacts of neonicotinoid insecticides on insect pollinators
indicated considerable harm. However, lingering criticism was that the studies did not
represent field-realistic levels of the chemicals or prevailing environmental
conditions. Two studies, conducted on different crops and on two continents, now
